ibrary at Nanterre</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_44563b58ed65ce215ae215d3865c4554" level="file"><did><unittitle>PRO - PREM 314 + FO</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1945/1945">1945</unitdate><container id="aspace_fa27616451acdf4f7647d47b4bc04ccf" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_ab0b6fc3c6374886cb71571685248e9d" parent="aspace_fa27616451acdf4f7647d47b4bc04ccf" type="folder">5-6</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_669fb89da0b2e7f65b08d266a15294ea"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Classified documents on French Indo-China from Public Records Office (Foreign Office documents)</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_40e26f05a69d014871b2b4106e486296" level="file"><did><unittitle>Mary Speers' Notes</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1942/1943" type="inclusive">1942-1943</unitdate><container id="aspace_2c46a43263635ee83d776a653f826521" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_98dbe46aac27d14142c6a0b38f92b8bc" parent="aspace_2c46a43263635ee83d776a653f826521" type="folder">7</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_2fb37c646720f4ad11ac37885ab965b4"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Foreign Office series 371/35921, ff. Mostly on wartime relations with France.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_66374441566d62f006507bd57881470f" level="file"><did><unittitle>My Notes 1980 - PRO &amp; Rhodes House</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1980/1980">1980</unitdate><container id="aspace_683c1f8db0e2a7dc08c85db5d518c3b7" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_a86ee501050802885aba21d4daf121d0" parent="aspace_683c1f8db0e2a7dc08c85db5d518c3b7" type="folder">8</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_15da68ac1d332fa320352b6d9de99815"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>CAB 121/741 - Notes taken on memos on Indochina for PM from Foreign Section. File: "My Notes 1980: PRO &amp; Roosevelt." CAB 120/56 - 121/741. Succinct notes of heart of documents re: French Indochina (ca. 40-50 pp.). Notebook cover headed "Cabinet Officers etc." has several pages of references to A. Creech Jones.</p><p> 2nd notebook: Rhodes Library Oxford - About 100 pp. of penciled notes on FO 371; CO 824 Register; CO 872-4-9 inclusive (1942, 1942) Mostly to FO 371/371779-90</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_882641775d4bd943c4046cce71f4aac7" level="file"><did><unittitle>DDE '54 - documents</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1954/1954">1954</unitdate><container id="aspace_3b2ee2d7ce8f603ca67cb7401295319a" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_499e29108c1bebfca2014f2423bec925" parent="aspace_3b2ee2d7ce8f603ca67cb7401295319a" type="folder">9</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_d4c4cd2d8b44f1177511b9a1ffa9da65"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Dwight D. Eisenhower Library</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_42adfae9cae0b88bcf98f8b0bf2e8c14" level="file"><did><unittitle>National Archives - Use of Indo China Resistance Forces</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1944/1945" type="inclusive">1944-1945</unitdate><container id="aspace_957d477a9855f5d7d0cbdb8e6e323e16" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_39676281a5677085d5993f40b54e184c" parent="aspace_957d477a9855f5d7d0cbdb8e6e323e16" type="folder">10-11</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_dbd8f8d86f47433c2d61b3b65e326d31" level="file"><did><unittitle>National Archives</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1941/1941">1941</unitdate><container id="aspace_ca0489f6f0ba0aee826f54ece3759bdb" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182382]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_7f8ead08eadc65189140e4f1f8c94d94" parent="aspace_ca0489f6f0ba0aee826f54ece3759bdb" type="folder">12</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_88f942e2113e